WITH `basic_ticket_dimensions_2` AS
(
	SELECT  `basic_ticket_dimensions`.`ticket`                         AS `ticket`
	       ,`basic_ticket_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_inbound_or_outbound` AS `dim_ticket_inbound_or_outbound`
	FROM `metrics_silver`.`dsrc__basic_ticket_dimensions__95b498dc05c9bd7e9a75f94c9de28177` AS `basic_ticket_dimensions`
	WHERE `basic_ticket_dimensions`.`ds` = '2023-09-08' 
), `ticket_team_dimensions_2` AS (
SELECT  `ticket_team_dimensions`.`ticket`                   AS `ticket`
       ,`ticket_team_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_is_payments`   AS `dim_ticket_is_payments`
       ,`ticket_team_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_team_category` AS `dim_ticket_team_category`
FROM `metrics_silver`.`dsrc__ticket_team_dimensions__0eee45ad71aa774094eaf812a2748490` AS `ticket_team_dimensions`
WHERE `ticket_team_dimensions`.`ds` = '2023-09-08' ), `user_location_geo_2` AS (
SELECT  `user_location_geo`.`user`               AS `user`
       ,`user_location_geo`.`dim_origin_country` AS `dim_origin_country`
       ,`user_location_geo`.`ts_start`           AS `ts_start`
       ,`user_location_geo`.`ts_end`             AS `ts_end`
FROM `metrics_silver`.`dsrc__user_location_geo__83f2487002081c93bd467adbf6789661` AS `user_location_geo`
WHERE `user_location_geo`.`ds` = '2023-09-08' )
SELECT  CAST(DATE_SUB(DATE_TRUNC('week',DATE_ADD(CAST(`cs_tickets`.`ds` AS DATETIME),INTERVAL 1 DAY)),INTERVAL 1 DAY) AS DATETIME) AS `__timestamp`
       ,COALESCE( SUM( CASE WHEN `basic_ticket_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_inbound_or_outbound` IN ('inbound','unknown') AND `ticket_team_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_is_payments` = 'True' AND `ticket_team_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_team_category` = 'Refund' AND NOT `ticket_team_dimensions`.`dim_ticket_team_category` IS NULL THEN `cs_tickets`.`cs_tickets` ELSE NULL END ),0 ) AS `cs_payments_refund_inbound_tickets`
FROM `minerva`.`esrc__cs_tickets__573c06282b6f8cb162f1a6eb20525f4c` AS `cs_tickets`
LEFT JOIN `basic_ticket_dimensions_2` AS `basic_ticket_dimensions`
ON `cs_tickets`.`ticket` <> '0' AND `cs_tickets`.`ticket` = `basic_ticket_dimensions`.`ticket` AND NOT `cs_tickets`.`ticket` IS NULL
LEFT JOIN `ticket_team_dimensions_2` AS `ticket_team_dimensions`
ON `cs_tickets`.`ticket` <> '0' AND `cs_tickets`.`ticket` = `ticket_team_dimensions`.`ticket` AND NOT `cs_tickets`.`ticket` IS NULL
LEFT JOIN `user_location_geo_2` AS `user_location_geo`
ON `cs_tickets`.`ts` <= `user_location_geo`.`ts_end` AND `cs_tickets`.`ts` >= `user_location_geo`.`ts_start` AND `cs_tickets`.`user` <> '0' AND `cs_tickets`.`user` = `user_location_geo`.`user` AND NOT `cs_tickets`.`user` IS NULL
WHERE `cs_tickets`.`ds` <= '2023-09-08'
AND CAST(`cs_tickets`.`ds` AS DATE) < STR_TO_DATE('2023-08-14T00:00:00', '%Y-%m-%dT%T')
AND CAST(`cs_tickets`.`ds` AS DATE) >= STR_TO_DATE('2022-06-20T00:00:00', '%Y-%m-%dT%T')
AND COALESCE(`user_location_geo`.`dim_origin_country`, '-unknown-') IN ('FR')
GROUP BY  CAST(DATE_SUB(DATE_TRUNC('week',DATE_ADD(CAST(`cs_tickets`.`ds` AS DATETIME),INTERVAL 1 DAY)),INTERVAL 1 DAY) AS DATETIME)
ORDER BY `cs_payments_refund_inbound_tickets` DESC
LIMIT 50000;

table_meta.metrics_silver.dsrc__basic_ticket_dimens:
CREATE  TABLE `dsrc__basic_ticket_dimensions__95b498dc05c9bd7e9a75f94c9de28177` (
  `ticket` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "CX ticket ID",
  `dim_ticket_zendesk_group` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Name of the current Zendesk group of a ticket: Community Education, Resolutions 1, Resolutions 2, etc",
  `dim_ticket_zendesk_group_first` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Name of the FIRST zendesk group of a ticket (Community Education, Resolutions 1, Resolutions 2, etc). Only used for tracking ticket routing behavior and NOT for CS metrics reporting.",
  `dim_ticket_guest_host` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Host or guest status from reservation code if it exists, or from custom10 if not: host, guest, NULL",
  `dim_ticket_has_homes_reservation` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Denotes whether a ticket has a linked Homes reservation",
  `dim_ticket_has_experiences_reservation` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Denotes whether a ticket has a linked Experiences reservation",
  `dim_ticket_business_unit` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The Business Unit (BU) that a ticket is attributed to.  Logic is based on the Monami user country at the time of ticket creation.",
  `dim_ticket_tier` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Name of the ticket tier; prior to May 15th, 2019, it uses magical, nontrip, other, px, and trip; since May 15, 2019 to June 27, 2021, it uses the ticket topic -> tier mapping. Since June 28, 2021, it uses contact reason -> tier mapping.",
  `dim_ticket_service_type` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Name of the service type based on dim_is_ booleans",
  `dim_ticket_service_group` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The service tier of a ticket based on the current zendesk group (Community Education, Resolutions 1, Resolutions 2, etc). Historic Safety and Claims tickets are based on legeacy dim_is_safety/dim_is_claims flags.",
  `dim_ticket_service_group_first` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The service tier of a ticket based on the FIRST zendesk group (Community Education, Resolutions 1, Resolutions 2, etc). Only used for tracking ticket routing behavior and NOT for CS metrics reporting.",
  `dim_ticket_status` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Status of the ticket: New, Solved, Closed, Open, Pending, Deleted",
  `dim_ticket_user_issue` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The user issue associated with the ticket: cancellations::host cancellation, cancellations::refund requests, miscellaneous::other::no tag,...",
  `dim_ticket_user_issue_parent` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The parent user issue associated with the ticket. Everything to the left of the first semi colon in the dim_cx_user_issue field",
  `dim_ticket_topic_parent` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The parent ticket topic node (e.g. highest level) associated with the ticket. This is the top-level issue associated with a ticket, e.g. Billing, Hosting, Account, etc... Populated for every ticket that has a ticket topic assigned",
  `dim_ticket_topic_child` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The ticket topic child node associated with the ticket. Populated for every ticket that has a ticket topic assigned",
  `dim_ticket_topic_grandchild` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The ticket topic grandchild node associated with the ticket. Not populated for all ticket topic paths, e.g. some paths are only parent and child",
  `dim_ticket_topic_name` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The terminal ticket topic node associated with the ticket. This can be either the child or grandchild depending on the depth of the ticket topic",
  `dim_ticket_topic_path` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The full ticket topic path associated with the ticket-- parent, child, and grandchild (if populated)",
  `dim_ticket_topic_cluster` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The grouping of ticket topic path associated with ticket",
  `dim_ticket_is_neighborhood_complaint` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Whether the ticket topic path falls under neighborhood complaints, defined as containing 'parties' or equal to 'Reservations - Conflict and communication - Neighbor complaints' for tickets created before 2021-06-28.  Whether the contact reason path falls under neighborhood complaints, defined as containing 'Reporting a party or event in an Airbnb listing' OR dim_contact_reason_path = 'Safety, discrimination, and violations reports -  Reporting violations of Airbnb's standards - Neighbor complaint' for tickets created since 2021-06-28.",
  `dim_ticket_inbound_or_outbound` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Whether the ticket is Inbound (initiated by user) or Outbound (initiated by agent)",
  `dim_ticket_is_cs` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "A flag indicating if the ticket is in a set of groups corresponding to CS issues",
  `dim_ticket_is_ghosted` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Denotes whether a ticket is flagged as ghosted by CS. Ghosted tickets are excluded from some Safety and Claims metrics (CSAT, CSAT resolution rate..).",
  `dim_ticket_is_directly_solved` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Denotes if a ticket is solved by a Community Expert (e.g. through the Directly program)",
  `dim_ticket_is_directly_routed` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Denotes if a ticket was routed to a Community Expert (e.g. through the Directly program). Ticket may or may not be solved by Directly",
  `dim_ticket_language` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The primary language (e.g. preferred language on profile) of the ticket filer",
  `dim_ticket_creator_role` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "ticket creator role including agent",
  `dim_ticket_ts_created_at` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Timestamp of ticket creation",
  `dim_ticket_ds_created_at` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Date of ticket creation",
  `dim_ticket_ts_solved_at` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Timestamp of ticket solve",
  `dim_ticket_ds_solved_at` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Date of ticket solve",
  `dim_ticket_ts_closed_at` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Timestamp of ticket close",
  `dim_ticket_is_party` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The CS ticket either has ticket topic or tags signifying a party occurred during the reservation",
  `dim_contact_reason_parent` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The parent contact reason node (e.g. highest level) associated with the ticket. This is the top-level issue associated with a ticket. Populated for every ticket  that has a ticket topic assigned",
  `dim_contact_reason_child` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The contact reason child node associated with the ticket. ",
  `dim_contact_reason_grandchild` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The contact reason grandchild node associated with the ticket. Not populated for all contact reason paths, e.g. some paths are only parent and child",
  `dim_contact_reason_name` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The terminal contact reason node associated with the ticket. This can be either the child or grandchild depending on the depth of the contact reason",
  `dim_contact_reason_path` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "The full contact reason path associated with the ticket-- parent, child, and grandchild (if populated)",
  `ds` varchar(1048576) NULL COMMENT "Minerva Date Stamp"
) ENGINE=OLAP 
DUPLICATE KEY(`ticket`)
COMMENT "OLAP"
DISTRIBUTED BY HASH(`ticket`) BUCKETS 10 
PROPERTIES (
"replication_num" = "1",
"in_memory" = "false",
"storage_format" = "DEFAULT",
"enable_persistent_index" = "false",
"compression" = "LZ4"
);
